<title>ESTONIA: AVERAGE WAGE UP 18.4 PCT IN Q1.</title>
<headline>AVERAGE WAGE UP 18.4 PCT IN Q1.</headline>
<dateline>TALLINN 1997-05-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Estonia's average monthly gross wage was 3,136 kroons in the first quarter of this year, an increase of 18.4 percent compared to the same period in 1996, the country's statistics office said on Wednesday.  </p>
<p>The average gross wage per hour was 19.15 kroons, it added in a statement.</p>
<p>The gross wage in the finance sector was 2.3 times higher than the average wage.  </p>
<p>The lowest gross wages were in agriculture and hunting which were 54.7 percent of the average gross wage.</p>
<p>-- Eva Palu, Tallinn Newsroom, +372 630 8400, reuters@reuters.ee</p>
